# shadcn/ui Conventions

## 1. Component Ownership & Modification
* **Modify Directly:** Treat shadcn/ui components as part of the local codebase. You are explicitly encouraged to open, modify, extend, or alter the component file under `components/ui/` to meet specific design requirements or feature mandates.
* **Keep Core Primitives:** When modifying a component, ensure you do not break the underlying Radix UI accessible primitive hooks or structural requirements (like `forwardRef` or accessibility tags).

## 2. Installation & Directory Layout
* **CLI Management:** Always use your designated package manager prefix (e.g., `bun x shadcn-ui add [component]`) to pull down new primitives rather than manually copy-pasting code from the documentation site.
* **Isolation:** Keep primitive UI elements locked strictly inside the `components/ui/` subfolder. Composite components or complex layout structures (e.g., `Navbar`, `Sidebar`) must live outside the `ui/` boundary.

## 3. Consistency & Styling
* **Utility Synergy:** Leverage the existing global `cn()` utility (which wraps `clsx` and `tailwind-merge`) whenever adding or passing dynamic external class overrides down to a shadcn primitive.
* **Design Consistent Variants:** When adding custom button styles, badges, or sizes, update the `cva` (Class Variance Authority) configurations at the top of the component file instead of layering messy conditionals inside the TSX/JSX block.
